{{it/Manual/Tutorial/Tutorial}}
Benvenuto nel tutorial di gioco generale di OpenTTD. Qui ti sarà mostrato come iniziare a giocare e come cotruire linee di autobus e treni.  Probabilmente ci metterai circa 30 minuti. Se sei in dubbio, clicca con il tasto destro su un bottone del gioco per sapere a cosa serve.  Il menù a destra mostra tutorial più dettagliati su aspetti più specifici del gioco, in cui potrai cercare se c'è qualcosa di più specifico che vuoi imparare.
==Starting the game==
{{en/Phototable|[[File:en/Manual/Main menu new game.png|Main menu]]|Menù principale di OpenTTD|center}}
Dopo aver avviato il gioco, ti verrà mostrato il menù principale.


*Click the '''New Game''' button. This will open the World Generation screen, filled with even more dazzling options. Leave these to their defaults for now.
{{en/Phototable|[[File:en/Manual/Worldgenerationdialog.png|World Generation dialog]]|The World Generation dialog. The four images at the top allow you to change the climate. We'll leave all options the way they are for this tutorial.|center}}

*Click the big green '''Generate''' button. The game will now create a new world for you to play in, and the game will start.

==Inside the game==
{{en/Phototable|[[File:en/Manual/Tutorial/Aftergamestart.png|after the start]]|Right after the start of a new game.|right}}
The screen you now see is what you'll be playing all of OpenTTD in. In the middle you can see the green landscape, perhaps with an industry, town or forest here and there. This is the world you'll be taming using the tools of your trade: roads, railways, docks and airports. 

At the top of the screen you'll notice a menu bar. Right click some of the buttons - a popup will appear to tell you about what the button does. Some of the buttons have menus under them. You can access the menu options by holding down the left mouse button, moving down the menu and releasing on the option you want.
